# e2e-hunter project notes

Copy this file to `e2e/HUNTER_NOTES.md` at your project root and fill in the
sections that matter for your project. Leave unused sections empty or delete
them. e2e-hunter reads this before Phase 0 on every run.

All sections are optional. Bullet points work well — plain prose also works.
Claude parses semi-structured content and applies it to the right phase.

---

## Scope

Applied in Phase 1 (scanning) and Phase 2 (scenario matrix).
List areas the skill should NOT test or scan.

<!-- examples:
- Ignore all auth/login flows — being replaced by Azure AD B2C
- Skip RBAC / role-permission checks
- Don't scan the `legacy-admin/` directory
- Exclude internal health/metrics endpoints (`/api/_status`, `/api/metrics`)
-->

## Focus

Applied in Phase 2 (boost matrix priority) and Phase 4 (more scenarios generated).
List areas you want deeper-than-default coverage for.

<!-- examples:
- Service-request per-document submission/review flow (PER_DOCUMENT review mode)
- Document upload + admin review cross-app flow (happy path + rejection)
- Candidate assessment questionnaire round-trip (data integrity)
- Messaging: two-way conversation, read receipts, attachments
-->

## Constraints

Applied in Phase 7 (fix-and-retest loop).
List "do not touch" rules and guardrails for automated fixes.

<!-- examples:
- Do not modify `backend/src/modules/auth/**` — being rewritten
- Only apply backend fixes ≤ 20 LOC; larger fixes must be proposed not applied
- Never modify `*.env*` files
- No database migrations; schema changes require a PR discussion
- Do not touch anything under `legacy/`
-->

## Known dev-mode quirks

Applied in Phase 6 (bug classification).
List "this isn't a bug" behaviors so they get tagged `KNOWN_QUIRK` instead
of `API_BUG` / `UI_BUG`.

<!-- examples:
- MockAuthGuard auto-logs-in as dev-super when no auth header is present
  (backend/src/modules/auth/guards/mock-auth.guard.ts:178)
- Synthetic mock user UUIDs not in `users` table → 500 on mutations that
  stamp created_by. Workaround: use X-Mock-User-Email with a real seeded email.
- candidate portal labels "/service-requests" as "Visa Applications"
  (intentional candidate-facing terminology)
-->

## Test-readiness notes

Applied in Phase 1E (scoring) and Phase 2 (generation strategy).
Optional — only add entries here when you want to override the automatic scan.

<!-- examples:
- TreatAsGreen: components/LegacyDialog.tsx — we know it has unusual selectors
  but the test fixture below covers them explicitly
- TreatAsRed: components/OldWizard.tsx — schedule for data-testid audit in Q2,
  accept mount-only tests until then
- RequiredFixture: `e2e/fixtures/pdf/small.pdf` — used by upload dialog tests;
  regenerate by running `node scripts/gen-fixtures.js`
- SeededData: these tests require at least one candidate with each document
  variant attached — run `npm run seed:variants` before Phase 5
-->

